  "ciliary_role": "Known ciliopathy gene CORD13. Mutations are known causes of RP and Leber congenital amaurosis. Potential structural component of the ciliary axoneme, which anchors RPGR within the cilium (11104772, 15772089). Required for disk morphogenesis and RPGR retention in the connecting cilium (12651948). Essential for rod OS formation, probably by regulating the transport of proteins from the IS to the OS (19679561). Required for ciliary targeting of NPHP4 and SDCCAG8, Rab8 localisation in photoreceptors and is involved in rhodopsin ciliary vesicle transport in zebrafish (29203866).",
